@hjk41 I've faced similar problem as @yunge and the new version fixes the issue. Now I'm able to compile and run MXNet on Windows (Only CPU).

I use Intel Parallel Studio Xe 2016 + VS2013 + OpenCV3.0 + Canopy. The `cmake` command should be like `cmake -DOpenCV_DIR=YOUR_OPENCV_DIR -DBLAS=MKL ..` and the resulting VS2013 project should be configured to 64 bit. Also, to make the python package find the dll, the [dll path generation code](https://github.com/dmlc/mxnet/blob/master/python/mxnet/libinfo.py#L18-L29) should be changed accordingly.  Moreover, since EPD has a pre-install openmp library that conflicts with the new MKL, I use the solution described [here](https://github.com/JoFrhwld/FAVE/wiki/Troubleshooting-FAVE-extract). 

Hope my experience can help others who are installing MXNet on Windows.

